<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Sinist</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-15 01:21:19</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I have to agree with Cloudburst. I happen to come across Bildge and killed him. Droped the Totem. 15 min later he spawns again and got the belt. Talk about lucky huh? As for level. He was blue to me at 40 and does heal himself pretty quickly if you can't keep up with the dmg. I had to totally unload on him at full mana to take him down and walked away with about 1 bub of mana and 2 bubs of health. He hits for about 50 or so dmg with double attacks and shoots arrows at you.(Depends on your stats too as to how hard he hits you) So I can image it would be hard for a melee class to take him down considering he takes off running at 1/2 health with out root or snare casted on him. Casters or Druid solo at 40ish easy or melee with caster back up no problems. I have no idea about the spawn times because like I said I just stumbled upon him. I do know that his path does cross the island in the middle because this is where I killed him a second time. I would image he spawns in the water somewhere or even on the far ends of the middle island. Who knows. Item worth?? Not sure cause I am certainly not gonna give up this item. The neg 9 str sucks but hey...What are the str buffs for anyways. More the worth the +18 wis. Hope this helps.</font></td></tr></table>
