<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Cloudburst</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-07 13:04:04</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Haven't checked back here in a while and I see my name is dragged through the mud!  Just joking, of course.  However, I must comment on Panther's post at the top of the page about the Fab Four attacking Dwigus.  All I can say is that I have come across Big D standing right in the fire of the Fab Four camp, some little level twelve crumbled corpse at his feet, and the four NPCs we just standing there.  When the dead fella comes back, he confirms that the four did nothing to assist him ("much to my dismay" he said, which I thought amusing).<BR>
<BR>
Panther says he saw the four attack Dwigus.  Sure, why not?  Perhaps Dwigus spawns at different levels and he's on the cusp of being ignored by the NPCs (too high level).  I'm just reporting what I saw.  <BR>
<BR>
I certainly, however, think it foolish to spend hours in DC looking for Bilge or Dwigus if you (or party) are not strong enough to take him.  You hope to make it back to the NPC camp (Bilge rooted me once) and hope you get the last lick in when all four NPCs are swinging like mad?  Hmmm, seems to me your best bet is to spend those hours getting experience so that you can go back to DC when you are ready to solo.  I can't imagine the frustration level if you spend all day finding Bilge, only to have him disappear when the NPCs attack.  And I need not even comment on the above option if you don't have SoW.  I've seen Dwigus own a well equiped 41 warrior.  Yaks, FBSS, the works.  Don't even think you can run very far un-SoWed with Dwigus on your fanny.<BR>
<BR>
Cheers.<BR>
<BR>
Cloudburst<BR>
Elders of Wisdom<BR>
Level 51 Druid<BR>
Veeshan</font></td></tr></table>
